headline: UCLA Undergraduate Computer Science Student
description: During my years as a student at Freedom High School, I was extremely involved in organizations on campus and also off-campus. For example, as the Assistant Director of The East Bay Saxophone Project (EBSP), a volunteer-based nonprofit organization that provides free music lessons to students in grades four through twelve, I prepared dynamic class plans for approximately one hundred students. Since the program has a large scope, I was also in charge of the website and home communication. My community participation extends to Veterans of Foreign Wars Post 10789 where I act as a technology consultant and to Global Glimpse as a former student ambassador to incorporate new volunteers. In October 2019, I joined Bet Tzedek as a Customer Intake Intern. I conduct legal interviews and connect our new clients to pro bono professionals.
job_description1: Unpaid volunteer internship for Bet Tzedek Legal Services
job_description2: A program for past-travelers to assist in the onboarding process for new volunteers. The primary responsibilities included recruitment and training.
job_description3: The East Bay Saxophone Project (EBSP) is a non-profit volunteer organization that provides free music lessons to students ranging from fourth to twelfth grade
job_description4: I started ZP Tech Services in the eighth grade, offering computer support and consulting services to my local area. My most notable clients include VFW Post 10789, Drea Lyn Photography, and GTA Mobile.
school_description2: Online Distance Education course - Criminal Justice 201GPA - 4.0
allSkills: Leadership, Technology Consulting, Nonprofit Organizations, Event Planning, Research, Social Media, Legal Assistance, Technical Support, Microsoft Office, Microsoft Excel, Microsoft Word, Microsoft PowerPoint, Java, Windows, Mac, Adobe Acrobat, C++, Team Building, Customer Service, Public Speaking, Time Management, Spanish, English

headline: Student at University of California, Los Angeles
job_description1: Full Stack Engineering Intern responsible for development of company frontend and backend system automation, user interface, and customer/client management database. Utilized Vue.js, ElementUI, Spring Boot, and MySQL frameworks.

headline: Undergrad Software Engineer at UCLA
description: An avid computer scientist, in the past I've built a smart home system in my college dorm, designed a DAQ on a NASA glider, and much more. Also skilled in UX/UI design. Whether it be a personal project or an internship job, I explore how CS and design can merge to provide an optimal experience for the end user. Currently an undergrad studying Computer Science & Engineering, hoping to find a career as a software engineer or a similar profession.
job_description1: Officer of UCLA ACM Design, a branch of ACM at the University of California, Los Angeles. Along with other officers, I am responsible for: -Maintaining the branch's official website -Maintaining the branding guidelines for all of our webpages, posters, logos, etc. -Hosting workshops, such as intro to UX/UI design.
job_description2: *More details at www.fukazawa.website Moirai Media is a new startup media company based in India. It offers services to help celebrities boost their public recognition and monetary income, such as managing promotional campaigns, setting up online commerce stores, landing sponsorship deals, etc. Despite it being less than a year old (as of 2019) it has already established contracts with many top-tier Indian celebrities such as Jacquline Fernadez and Anushka Sen. -Configured back-end for website and email on AWS -Redesigned the official website(moiraimedia.in) -Established a branding identity for the company -Set up a branding process to create personal brands for clients
job_companyName3: NASA - National Aeronautics and Space Administration
job_description3: *More details at www.fukazawa.website Member of the PRANDTL-D research team at Armstrong Flight Research Center, which tested a new glider wing design that theoretically improves flight efficiency. I was mainly responsible for developing a Data Acquisition System(DAQ) to go onboard the glider used in the research. Notable accomplishments: -Designed a new Data Acquisition System for the glider used in research -Improved theoretical precision of collected data by ~31% -Upgraded code to store data securely and prevent potential data loss -Reduced data file size by ~50% -Optimized code for hardware, e.g. direct manipulation of microchip registers -Developed a CLI tool to easily transfer data from DAQ to MatLab/Excel
job_companyName4: PVNet Education & Emerging Technology Center, Non-Profit 501c3 Corporation
job_description4: PVNet is a non-profit organization that holds various programs to educate youth on STEM subjects. I started in 2015 as a volunteer, and was later promoted to an internship as instructor. -Taught over 50 students 3D modeling, web design, game development, etc.
job_description5: Strategoi is a legal political non-profit founded by students to spread political awareness in the United States. -Constructed the official website and designed the logo.
allSkills: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), Computer-Aided Design (CAD), Adobe Photoshop, Web Development, Web Design, Maya, Github, Visual Studio, C, C++, Python, HTML, Cascading Style Sheets (CSS), JavaScript, Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, Firebase, Amazon Web Services (AWS), Java, PHP, SolidWorks, Blender, Atom, Eagle PCB
